Title

Implement MongoDB Verification Tests for Third-Party Synchronization Flow (Local)

Background

Current Journey Tests do not validate whether Third-Party configuration changes are correctly synchronized and persisted in MongoDB. Successful Journey Test execution does not verify runtime state consistency for create, update, or delete operations.

This story introduces database-level validation to directly verify synchronization outcomes.

Objective

Implement Playwright-based integration tests that validate MongoDB state after Third-Party synchronization execution.

Scope

In Scope

* Playwright test implementation
* MongoDB verification
* Local environment execution
* Test data setup and cleanup

Out of Scope

* Union environment implementation
* Rehearsal environment implementation
* Pipeline/Drivetrain changes
* Journey Test removal story
* Changes to synchronization logic
* Changes to OBA configuration structure

Acceptance Criteria

AC1 - Create Synchronization Validation

* Add a new TPP configuration.
* Execute synchronization process.
* Verify MongoDB record is created.
* Verify TPP ID, Client ID, Status, Permissions/Scopes match configuration values.

AC2 - Update Synchronization Validation

* Modify permissions/scopes for an existing TPP configuration.
* Execute synchronization process.
* Verify MongoDB record is updated.
* Verify updated permissions/scopes match configuration values.
* Verify unrelated fields remain unchanged.

AC3 - Delete Synchronization Validation

* Remove an existing TPP configuration.
* Execute synchronization process.
* Verify MongoDB record is removed or marked inactive as per current implementation.
* Verify no stale TPP data remains.

AC4 - Synchronization Idempotency Validation

* Execute synchronization multiple times without configuration changes.
* Verify no duplicate MongoDB records are created.
* Verify database state remains unchanged across executions.

Definition of Done

* Playwright tests implemented.
* MongoDB assertions implemented.
* Local execution successful.
* Test data cleanup implemented.
* Test evidence attached to Jira.
* Documentation updated.
